  "publisher": "dc",
  "about": "In biology, offspring () are the young creation of living organisms, produced either by sexual or asexual reproduction. Collective offspring may be known as a brood or progeny. This can refer to a set of simultaneous offspring, such as the chicks hatched from one clutch of eggs, or to all offspring produced over time, as with the honeybee.  Offspring can occur after mating, artificial insemination, or as a result of cloning.\nHuman offspring (descendants) are referred to as children; male children are sons and female children are daughters (see Kinship).",
  "note": null,
